    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, the way to store extra information about an extramark is by creating a separate table and manually adding/deleting extramarks with some data. This makes using extramarks a lot harder.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExtramarks would get a new field that could be any vim-type and would only be used by plugins and UIs.",
    "closed_at": "2024-01-06T21:31:27Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "What would be the use case? Note that extmarks are _extremely_ performance sensitive, so potentially heavy payloads must have a very strong justification. ",
