        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think the extra complexity here is justified and the use cases aren't strong enough. Extmarks are mainly intended for decorations.\n\nI don't see a problem with the current way of storing data in a table. What are the problems with that, and how does storing this data in extmarks solve such problems?\n\n> Extramarks would get a new field that could be any vim-type and would only be used by plugins and UIs.\n\nNote vim-types (aka typval) is not the same as Lua types so this would require conversion via the vimscript bridge.\n",
